---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="services -- alexander campos" description="Local-first AI infrastructure consulting. ForgeFrame setup, agent architecture, memory system design.">
  <article>
    <h1>What I Build</h1>

    <p>
      I build local-first AI infrastructure. If you need memory that persists,
      models that route without bleeding money, or systems that run on
      your hardware instead of someone else's — I can help.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <div class="services">

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>ForgeFrame Setup & Integration</h2>
        <p>
          Deploy persistent memory infrastructure for your AI agents. MCP-native,
          SQLite-backed, works with Claude Desktop, Cursor, or any MCP client.
          Session management, strength decay, constitutional memory — configured
          for your workflow.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Agent Infrastructure</h2>
        <p>
          Model routing across Anthropic, OpenAI, and Ollama. Tier-based dispatch
          with cost optimization (40-60% reduction). Provider adapters, structured
          tool-use, streaming SSE normalization. Built to run on your stack, not mine.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Local-First Architecture Consulting</h2>
        <p>
          Audit your AI stack for cloud dependencies. Design a migration path to
          local-first or hybrid architecture. Sovereignty review: what data leaves
          the machine, what doesn't need to, and what's at risk if it does.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <h2>Memory System Design</h2>
        <p>
          Custom semantic memory for your application. FTS5 search, embedding
          integration, weighted retrieval with decay. Not a vector DB — a memory
          system with opinions about what matters and what fades.
        </p>
        <a data-cal-link="alexcampos/30min" class="cta">Book a call &rarr;</a>
      </div>

    </div>

    <hr />

    <p class="pricing">
      Pricing depends on scope. Most engagements start with a 30-minute call.
    </p>

    <p class="contact-alt">
      Prefer email? <a href="mailto:adc.acampos@gmail.com">adc.acampos@gmail.com</a>
    </p>
  </article>

  <script is:inline src="/islands/cal-embed.js"></script>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c the infrastructure is the product. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .services {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .service-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--white-08);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .service-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--gold-accent);
  }

  .service-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .service-card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cta {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--gold-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--gold-accent);
    cursor: pointer;
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .cta:hover {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
    border-bottom-color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .pricing {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .contact-alt {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--white-30);
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
